paragraph.content:
the vesting of the rights, assets, liabilities and obligations of the
                    Construction Industry Training Authority in the Construction Industry
                    Council;

if no authorized person is appointed under that section, the person
                        appointed in accordance with section 66 in respect of the
                        construction operations;

subsection.def:
building (建築物) has
                the meaning assigned to it in section 2(1) of the Buildings Ordinance
                    (Cap. 123);

construction contract (建造合約) means a contract between an employer and a
                contractor under which the contractor carries out construction operations but does
                not include a contract of employment;

employer (聘用人)
                means a person for whom a contractor carries out construction operations, whether
                under a contract or otherwise;

value (價值), in
                relation to any construction operations, means the value of the construction
                operations as determined under section 52;

paragraph.content:
4 are to be persons who, in the opinion of the Council, represent
                        professionals or consultants connected with the construction
                        industry;

one is to be a person who, in the opinion of the Council, represents a
                        training institute or tertiary educational institution connected with the
                        construction industry;

the power to approve programmes of its proposed activities, estimates
                        of its income and expenditure or other statements or reports required to be
                        submitted to the Council;
